<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="582" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,727,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Shi, 2016" authorityName="Wang &amp; Shi" authorityYear="2016" box="[626,1128,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Nigrimacula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[626,916,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Nigrimacula sichuanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, H. J. &amp; Shi, F. M." box="[921,1128,727,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582" pagination="591 - 593" refId="ref2752" refString="Wang, H. J. &amp; Shi, F. M. (2016) One new species of the genus Nigrimacula Shi, Bian &amp; Zhou, 2016 (Orthoptera: Meconematinae) from Sichuan, China. Zootaxa, 4132 (4), 591 - 593. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4132.4.11" type="journal article" year="2016">Wang &amp; Shi, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but it differs from the latter in: apical half of male cercus compressed, slightly concave on inner surface, spoon-shaped, ventral margin slightly widened inwards in apical half; male subgenital plate nearly circular, apical area narrow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
