<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="582" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,871,897]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of new species is named for apical half of male cercus slightly widened inwards on ventral margin, from Latin ‘ 
<emphasis box="[425,481,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">platy</emphasis>
-’ (wide) and ‘ 
<emphasis box="[642,689,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">cerc</emphasis>
-’ (cercus).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
